The theme type detection is not reactive to theme changes. Calling `getColorTheme()` directly only reads the current theme at the moment of evaluation, but won't trigger re-computation when the theme changes. This means that if a user switches between high contrast and regular themes, the border colors won't update accordingly.

To fix this, wrap the theme type check in an observable that listens to theme changes, similar to the pattern used in `inlineEditsSideBySideView.ts:348`. For example:

```typescript
const isHighContrast = observableFromEvent(this._themeService.onDidColorThemeChange, () => {
  const theme = this._themeService.getColorTheme();
  return theme.type === 'hcDark' || theme.type === 'hcLight';
}).read(reader);
```

