The `DisposableCallback` class is missing important disposable tracking infrastructure that's present in similar classes like `FunctionDisposable` and `MutableDisposable`. This includes:

1. An `_isDisposed` flag to prevent multiple disposals
2. A `trackDisposable(this)` call in the constructor for leak detection
3. A `markAsDisposed(this)` call in the `dispose()` method

Suggested implementation:
```typescript
class DisposableCallback<T> implements IDisposable {
	private _cb: ((e: T) => void) | undefined;
	private _isDisposed = false;

	constructor(cb: (e: T) => void) {
		this._cb = cb;
		trackDisposable(this);
	}

	dispose(): void {
		if (this._isDisposed) {
			return;
		}
		this._isDisposed = true;
		markAsDisposed(this);
		this._cb = undefined;
	}

	readonly handler = (val: T) => {
		return this._cb?.(val);
	};
}
```

Note: You'll need to import `trackDisposable` and `markAsDisposed` from `vs/base/common/lifecycle.js`.

